WEBVTT

00:43.261 --> 00:48.261
<font color="#ffff00">Provided by explosiveskull</font>
https://twitter.com/kaboomskull
M_I_SForEver

05:02.979 --> 05:05.415
I'm so happy.

05:05.448 --> 05:07.750
I didn't think I could
ever be this happy.

05:07.784 --> 05:09.585
Me neither.

05:10.285 --> 05:14.757
I'm gonna spend the rest of my
life making sure you're this happy.

05:14.791 --> 05:16.426
I appreciate the sentiment,

05:16.459 --> 05:18.461
but we both know
that's not possible.

05:18.494 --> 05:21.431
I can get pretty grouchy.

05:21.464 --> 05:24.567
Mmm.
And I'll love you through it.

05:38.313 --> 05:40.183
It's good to see it too, Terry.

05:41.084 --> 05:42.051
You married into this.

05:44.020 --> 05:46.723
- How old are you?
- Not as old as you, Grandpa.

05:49.525 --> 05:52.662
- Congratulations again, you two.
- Thanks, Chase.

05:52.695 --> 05:55.297
So, Chase, as my best man,

05:55.330 --> 05:57.033
I kinda need you
to do me a favor.

05:57.066 --> 05:59.902
- Name it.
- Yeah, get Terry away from my wife.

06:01.170 --> 06:04.040
- You got it.
- What? I'm only dancing.

06:04.073 --> 06:05.475
Shut up Terry.

06:08.444 --> 06:11.047
I'm sorry.
Where were we?

06:16.085 --> 06:18.020
- Babe, hold my earrings.
- Yeah.

06:18.054 --> 06:19.489
- They bothering you?
- A little bit.

06:19.522 --> 06:23.059
Okay. No problem, my love.

06:26.129 --> 06:28.698
Benny.

06:28.731 --> 06:31.134
- Benny? What?
- Hello, Grace.

06:32.769 --> 06:34.570
Lucas, honey, this is Benny.

06:36.606 --> 06:39.942
Yeah. Hey, Benny.
Grace told me all about you.

06:39.976 --> 06:42.445
It's, um...
It's nice to meet you.

06:42.478 --> 06:44.180
Likewise.

06:44.213 --> 06:46.849
And congratulations...
to both of you, that is.

06:46.883 --> 06:48.117
Thank you.

06:50.386 --> 06:52.354
So, Benny, I didn't know
you'd be attending.

06:53.456 --> 06:55.057
Oh, I see.

06:55.091 --> 06:58.261
I mean, I'm glad
to see you, though.

06:58.326 --> 07:00.196
I'm glad to see you too, Grace.

07:00.229 --> 07:01.864
And of course I'd attend.
How could I not?

07:03.633 --> 07:08.237
Hey, well, um, Benny,
thank you for stopping by.

07:08.271 --> 07:09.872
Yes, of course.

07:09.906 --> 07:11.774
Thanks for coming.
It's so good to see you.

07:11.808 --> 07:14.410
It's always nice
to see you, Grace.

07:14.443 --> 07:19.115
So, uh, Benny, Grace tells me you
haven't spoken in a few years.

07:19.148 --> 07:22.985
- What have you been up to?
- Oh, you know, this and that.

07:24.620 --> 07:26.823
- Brooklyn!
- Nice to see you!

07:28.758 --> 07:30.660
I... I'm gonna get
some more of those crab bites.

07:30.693 --> 07:33.095
Yeah, you, uh... you do that.

07:33.129 --> 07:35.298
- Did I interrupt something?
- Girl, you saved us.

07:35.330 --> 07:36.933
- Okay.
- Hey, Brook.

07:36.966 --> 07:38.568
- Hey, Luke.
- Thanks for coming.

07:38.601 --> 07:40.335
Oh, I wouldn't miss it
for the world.

07:41.871 --> 07:44.106
Can you believe I actually
got this guy down the aisle?

07:44.140 --> 07:47.610
No, I can't,
but I'm happy for you.

07:47.643 --> 07:49.312
I'm happy for both of you.

07:49.344 --> 07:51.180
I'm a blessed woman.

07:51.214 --> 07:53.115
When God gave out husbands,
He gave me the best.

07:53.149 --> 07:56.619
Yeah, He did.
Lucas is one of the good guys.

07:56.652 --> 07:59.589
Let's just keep that low 'cause I
have a reputation to keep, okay?

07:59.622 --> 08:01.290
Oh, don't worry,
your secret's safe with me.

08:01.324 --> 08:02.425
Yeah, me too.

08:04.460 --> 08:06.596
- It's our song.
- Sure is.

08:06.629 --> 08:08.431
Okay, I'll let you two
get back at it.

08:08.464 --> 08:10.600
I just wanted to say
congratulations.

08:10.633 --> 08:12.101
Thank you again.
I'll come find you in a bit.

08:12.134 --> 08:13.169
You better.

08:13.836 --> 08:16.005
- Bye, Luke.
- Bye, Brook.

08:19.041 --> 08:22.578
- I finally get to dance my wife.
- That's the plan, baby.

08:24.981 --> 08:27.383
So, I don't know
how to say this,

08:27.416 --> 08:29.886
so I'm just gonna say it.

08:29.919 --> 08:32.221
- Lucas, you son of a bitch.
- Oh, God.

08:32.255 --> 08:34.457
Please tell me that's not Mason.

08:34.490 --> 08:36.158
I'm sorry I can't do that.

08:36.192 --> 08:38.027
I thought you said
you didn't invite him.

08:38.059 --> 08:39.562
- I didn't.
- I don't think he knows that.

08:39.595 --> 08:41.563
I don't think he cares.

08:41.597 --> 08:44.667
Get over here!

08:44.700 --> 08:46.736
Congrats, man!
You're finally getting hitched.

08:46.769 --> 08:48.871
Thanks.

08:48.905 --> 08:51.574
And, Ms. Grace, please tell me
you know how lucky you are.

08:51.607 --> 08:54.243
This guy could have had anyone
he wanted and he chose you.

08:54.277 --> 08:56.279
She chose me.

08:57.880 --> 08:59.582
It's good to see you, Mason.

08:59.615 --> 09:01.651
Sorry I missed
the actual ceremony.

09:01.684 --> 09:04.320
Funny story... there's a chick
back at the airport...

09:04.353 --> 09:07.423
Okay, I think we all
how this story ends.

09:07.456 --> 09:09.892
Yeah, of course you do.
You taught me everything I know.

09:09.926 --> 09:12.828
Oh, Mason, my wedding,
we're at my wedding.

09:12.862 --> 09:15.498
Yeah, okay, you're right.
Sorry, Ms. Grace.

09:16.565 --> 09:18.501
I'm gonna let you boys
get caught up.

09:18.534 --> 09:19.902
Chase, care to dance?

09:19.936 --> 09:22.672
Darling, I thought
you'd never ask.

09:26.742 --> 09:28.711
I need a drink.
You need a drink?

09:28.744 --> 09:30.947
- Uh, I could...
- Let's grab a drink.

09:32.081 --> 09:33.149
Move!

09:42.925 --> 09:45.261
A toast to the man
no one thought

09:45.294 --> 09:47.630
would ever settle down,
settling down.

09:51.968 --> 09:53.369
- Ah!
- Oh.

09:54.136 --> 09:55.304
She's amazing, man.

09:55.338 --> 09:56.906
I gotta be honest,

09:56.939 --> 09:58.240
I don't know how I ever lived
without her.

09:58.274 --> 10:00.377
Oh, I do.

10:00.410 --> 10:02.645
But this is neither the time
or the place to talk about it.

10:02.678 --> 10:04.313
But seriously, bro,
I'm happy for you.

10:04.347 --> 10:06.282
Thanks, man.

10:06.315 --> 10:08.884
Lucas and Grace,
fricking married.

10:15.925 --> 10:18.160
I can't believe
you still remember that.

10:18.194 --> 10:20.663
Remember it?
Hell, I think I still got the scar from it.

10:20.696 --> 10:21.964
Oh...

10:22.798 --> 10:25.134
- Okay. Mm...
- Yep, got stabbed.

10:25.167 --> 10:27.236
And you wonder why
we don't hang out anymore.

10:28.537 --> 10:31.307
What I don't get is
you sleep with her sister,

10:31.340 --> 10:33.109
but I'm the one
that gets stabbed.

10:33.142 --> 10:35.811
What? No, no, I...
you slept with her sister.

10:35.845 --> 10:37.513
You just tried
to blame it on me.

10:37.546 --> 10:40.316
- Oh. That's right.
- Huh.

10:40.349 --> 10:42.318
So, wait, how'd she know
it was me, then?

10:42.351 --> 10:44.854
You sent her a picture
of you and her sister.

10:44.887 --> 10:47.523
- Yeah. What's that prove?
- You were naked.

10:47.556 --> 10:50.359
- So?
- And so was her sister.

10:50.394 --> 10:51.761
- Huh.
- Yeah.

10:51.794 --> 10:53.229
Well, I guess that proves it.

10:54.363 --> 10:55.598
You boys having fun?

10:55.631 --> 10:57.600
Mm, something like that.

10:57.633 --> 10:59.101
Well, I won't interrupt.

10:59.135 --> 11:00.936
Just needed a break
from my parents.

11:00.970 --> 11:03.339
- Oh, is it that bad?
- No, they're fine.

11:03.372 --> 11:05.274
But, I mean,
you know how they are.

11:05.307 --> 11:06.342
I do.

11:07.411 --> 11:08.445
Gentlemen.

11:10.079 --> 11:11.448
Madam.

11:11.481 --> 11:12.516
And where have you been?

11:14.316 --> 11:16.352
I was talking to Grace's
friend Tasha over there.

11:17.753 --> 11:19.822
She's a real sweetheart.

11:19.855 --> 11:21.824
You be good, Chase.

11:21.857 --> 11:23.059
Always, darling.

11:24.193 --> 11:26.796
I'll let you boys
get back to it.

11:26.829 --> 11:28.898
I'm gonna make one more trip around,
then I'm getting out of this dress.

11:28.931 --> 11:30.566
Whoa, I thought I was the one

11:30.599 --> 11:32.735
that got to get you
out of that dress later.

11:32.768 --> 11:35.004
You'll be getting me out of whatever
I'm wearing, don't you worry.

11:35.037 --> 11:36.872
Mmm...

11:36.906 --> 11:39.375
- Don't drink too much, okay?
- Mm.

11:39.409 --> 11:41.844
Don't worry Grace,
I'll take care of him.

11:41.877 --> 11:43.413
That's what I'm afraid of.

11:48.617 --> 11:53.322
So I'm almost afraid to ask
'cause... anyone seen Terry?

12:14.411 --> 12:15.778
I found him.

12:25.321 --> 12:28.124
Mason, thanks for showing
my husband a good time,

12:28.157 --> 12:29.593
but I think this is
where we say good night.

12:31.327 --> 12:34.630
I get it.
Time to consummate the marriage.

12:34.663 --> 12:37.434
Good night, Mason.

12:37.467 --> 12:39.436
Good night, Grace.

12:39.469 --> 12:41.637
- Mason!
- Yo.

12:41.670 --> 12:43.906
Cool seeing you tonight.

12:43.939 --> 12:46.942
Maybe I'll catch you
before you hop on the plane?

12:46.976 --> 12:49.812
Might need some alone time
with my wife.

12:49.845 --> 12:51.914
I love when you call me your wife.

12:51.947 --> 12:55.552
Yeah, we got
some baby-making to do.

12:55.585 --> 12:57.720
And you ruined it.

12:57.753 --> 12:59.623
Good night, Mason. Stay safe.

12:59.655 --> 13:02.057
I always am. No kids yet.

13:02.091 --> 13:05.094
It's not what I meant.

13:05.127 --> 13:07.229
What do you think you're doing?

13:07.263 --> 13:08.964
I'm driving.

13:08.998 --> 13:10.933
- You're not driving.
- It's my car.

13:10.966 --> 13:12.001
And you're drunk.

13:12.868 --> 13:14.837
I'm not that drunk.

13:14.870 --> 13:17.339
You're "I hate the ending
of <i>Game of Thrones</i>" drunk.

13:17.373 --> 13:19.576
Yeah, but at least he's not "I
can't believe the Ultimate Warrior

13:19.609 --> 13:22.077
beat Hulk Hogan
in WrestleMania VI" drunk.

13:22.111 --> 13:23.613
- Ugh!
- She got that going for it.

13:23.647 --> 13:25.748
Crap! That was crap!

13:25.781 --> 13:27.651
Oh, man, Ultimate Warrior!
Whoo!

13:27.683 --> 13:29.952
All right, babe,
you know what?

13:29.985 --> 13:33.122
You might be right.
You'll get us home faster.

13:33.155 --> 13:34.624
In a hurry to get home?

13:34.658 --> 13:35.858
You have no idea.

13:37.793 --> 13:39.596
That's my boy!

13:54.544 --> 13:56.078
This is married sex!

14:27.943 --> 14:30.580
Good morning, my beautiful wife.

14:30.614 --> 14:32.815
Good morning,
my adorable husband.

14:32.848 --> 14:34.750
- Mm.
- How'd you sleep?

14:34.783 --> 14:37.786
Great, and I'm even better now.

14:38.787 --> 14:39.989
Why is that?

14:41.257 --> 14:44.661
Because I get to wake up
next to you every morning

14:44.694 --> 14:46.429
for the rest of my life.

14:48.063 --> 14:50.833
I don't know
how I got so lucky,

14:50.866 --> 14:53.002
but I'm gonna thank God
every day that I did.

14:53.035 --> 14:56.171
Oh. I love you, Grace.

14:56.205 --> 14:57.474
I love you, Lucas.

15:03.647 --> 15:05.814
Babe, what's wrong?

15:07.249 --> 15:09.952
I just remembered we have to
meet my parents for breakfast.

15:09.985 --> 15:12.788
Oh, I forgot about that.

15:12.821 --> 15:16.859
Remind me again why we agreed to meet
with them the morning after our wedding.

15:16.892 --> 15:20.229
Uh, we... we didn't agree
to anything.

15:20.262 --> 15:23.633
You agreed,
and I got roped into this

15:23.667 --> 15:26.403
because of some new husband
clause or something.

15:26.436 --> 15:29.805
New? You make it sound
like I've had more than one.

15:29.838 --> 15:32.575
Well, you know there was
that tiny little guy, Benny,

15:32.609 --> 15:35.077
that chased you around,
nipping at your heels.

15:35.110 --> 15:37.414
- That was pretty serious.
- Oh!

15:37.447 --> 15:39.982
Are we forgetting how serious
you and Brooklyn were?

15:40.015 --> 15:44.754
Hmm. Hmm.

15:44.788 --> 15:46.589
Now what?

15:46.623 --> 15:47.657
Hi, Mom.

15:49.024 --> 15:50.794
Yep, 11:00, I know.
We'll be there.

15:52.495 --> 15:54.464
He didn't have
that much to drink, Mom.

15:54.497 --> 15:56.031
Begins already.

15:58.934 --> 16:01.136
Okay, okay,
we'll see you soon.

16:02.672 --> 16:04.708
Yeah, 11:00, I know.
You just told me.

16:07.444 --> 16:10.012
Okay, all right.

16:10.714 --> 16:13.248
See you soon. Bye.

16:14.818 --> 16:17.454
So in case you didn't know,
we're meeting my parents at 11:00.

16:17.487 --> 16:20.255
11:00? Wow, shocker!

16:21.491 --> 16:23.125
I'm gonna go for a jog
while you shower, okay?

16:23.158 --> 16:25.829
Why don't
we shower together?

16:25.894 --> 16:28.130
Honey, I may not
know everything,

16:28.163 --> 16:30.533
but one thing I do know is if
we get in that shower together,

16:30.567 --> 16:33.302
there's no way we're meeting
my parents at 11:00.

16:33.335 --> 16:35.438
And explain to me again
why that's a bad thing.

16:35.472 --> 16:37.474
Shower now.

16:37.507 --> 16:39.509
You now.

16:47.584 --> 16:51.554
Something tells me
we're not gonna make

16:51.588 --> 16:53.690
that lunch at 11:00.

16:53.723 --> 16:55.792
Something tells me
it'll be worth it.

17:14.209 --> 17:16.546
- Good morning.
- Morning. How's it going?

17:22.385 --> 17:26.188
I'm ready.
Can't say the same for you.

17:26.221 --> 17:27.824
Only because
you showered first.

17:29.626 --> 17:31.360
It's okay, I'll wait for you.

17:31.394 --> 17:33.763
Oh really? How nice of you.

17:33.797 --> 17:35.632
I would wait a lifetime for you.

17:41.303 --> 17:42.739
Babe, you okay?

17:44.407 --> 17:46.910
Yeah, I just got this sharp pain
in my head all of a sudden.

17:48.110 --> 17:52.615
Lucas,
something's wrong.

17:52.649 --> 17:54.417
Grace? Grace!

17:58.922 --> 18:00.590
Grace!

18:00.623 --> 18:02.157
No, baby! Honey!

18:02.958 --> 18:05.795
Grace? Grace!

18:05.829 --> 18:08.230
Stay with me, baby.

18:08.832 --> 18:11.568
Baby, wake up! Wake up!

18:11.601 --> 18:13.403
Grace!

18:13.436 --> 18:16.739
Somebody help me! Help!

18:16.773 --> 18:18.974
Grace. No.

18:22.579 --> 18:23.613
Grace!

18:27.182 --> 18:28.551
Please, God.

21:36.271 --> 21:38.641
Everything is going to be okay.

21:40.710 --> 21:41.744
Excuse me?

21:43.780 --> 21:46.348
Everything is going to be okay.

22:06.636 --> 22:07.937
Who was that?

22:07.970 --> 22:09.172
No idea.

22:10.873 --> 22:12.175
How you doing?

22:14.911 --> 22:17.547
My beautiful, vibrant wife

22:17.580 --> 22:19.982
just suddenly died
from a brain aneurysm.

22:20.016 --> 22:21.551
How do you think?

22:21.584 --> 22:23.820
Sorry, stupid question.

22:23.853 --> 22:25.655
Why are you here, Mason?

22:25.688 --> 22:27.190
'Cause, I'm your best friend.

22:29.025 --> 22:30.793
I might not be able
to make you feel any better,

22:30.827 --> 22:32.195
but I'm still gonna try.

22:35.665 --> 22:39.635
I just keep hoping
it's a bad dream...

22:41.170 --> 22:44.040
that I'm gonna wake up and...

22:46.109 --> 22:48.211
she's gonna be right next to me
where she belongs.

22:50.546 --> 22:51.681
I know, buddy.

22:52.949 --> 22:56.552
You know, the world ain't
all sunshine and rainbows.

22:58.020 --> 22:59.722
Did you seriously
just quote <i>Rocky</i> ?

23:00.757 --> 23:01.791
Sorry.

23:04.727 --> 23:08.064
Look, man, you can be
depressed tomorrow,

23:08.097 --> 23:12.068
but today you gotta go on there
and talk to Grace's parents,

23:12.101 --> 23:13.536
talk to her friends.

23:13.569 --> 23:15.138
You gotta be her husband.

23:16.606 --> 23:18.241
Does this even matter
at this point?

23:19.976 --> 23:21.244
What do you think
Grace would want?

23:23.412 --> 23:28.316
Mason, I'm literally about
to bury her in the ground.

23:29.552 --> 23:32.188
How would I possibly know
what she wants?

23:32.221 --> 23:34.791
Look, we both know
I don't believe in this crap...

23:37.560 --> 23:39.529
but you believe
she's up in heaven, right?

23:39.562 --> 23:40.596
That's just it.

23:42.330 --> 23:43.499
For me to believe in heaven,

23:44.667 --> 23:46.903
would mean I would have
to believe in a God

23:46.936 --> 23:48.271
that would kill my wife.

23:50.573 --> 23:52.475
So, the heavenly kid
doesn't believe in heaven.

23:53.176 --> 23:54.811
I'm not sure I do anymore.

23:56.612 --> 23:59.282
That's the funny thing
about you Christians.

23:59.314 --> 24:01.384
Y'all believe in God
when everything is good

24:01.417 --> 24:02.785
and there's nothing going wrong.

24:04.153 --> 24:06.589
And the minute
something bad happens,

24:06.622 --> 24:08.391
you start questioning
everything.

24:08.424 --> 24:10.726
Says the non-believer.

24:11.994 --> 24:13.029
Yeah, that's right.

24:13.963 --> 24:16.299
In my opinion,
there's no old man in the sky.

24:17.700 --> 24:19.902
But I know you believe
Grace is up there

24:19.936 --> 24:21.037
looking down on you.

24:22.805 --> 24:24.740
And I promise you,

24:24.774 --> 24:26.409
she is not happy
with you sitting out here

24:26.442 --> 24:27.977
feeling sorry for yourself.

24:30.546 --> 24:32.014
You're probably right.

24:32.048 --> 24:33.382
Yeah, I know.

25:00.243 --> 25:01.611
Lucas.

25:01.644 --> 25:03.012
Hey, Jackie.

25:06.582 --> 25:07.850
How are you holding up?

25:08.651 --> 25:09.785
I've been better.

25:10.887 --> 25:12.388
How about you?

25:12.421 --> 25:13.556
About the same.

25:14.991 --> 25:16.359
I'm really gonna miss Grace.

25:18.060 --> 25:19.929
Yeah, me too.

25:21.097 --> 25:23.366
It doesn't even
seem real, you know?

25:24.400 --> 25:25.868
I wish it wasn't real.

25:27.236 --> 25:28.771
I think I'll give
you two a minute.

25:32.174 --> 25:36.245
Do you wanna go somewhere
quiet, so we could talk?

25:36.279 --> 25:40.583
Oh, I'd love to, but I should
probably hang around here.

25:41.517 --> 25:44.086
I know.

25:44.120 --> 25:46.789
I just don't wanna break down
in front of all of these people.

25:50.927 --> 25:52.561
You know what? Uh...

25:52.595 --> 25:54.330
Come on, come on.

26:00.970 --> 26:02.305
Okay.

26:04.740 --> 26:05.775
All right.

26:07.411 --> 26:08.444
I think we're alone.

26:10.046 --> 26:11.415
Jackie, what are you doing?

26:12.448 --> 26:14.083
Jackie!

26:14.116 --> 26:16.852
- What?
- What do you mean, "What?"

26:16.886 --> 26:18.422
You don't like what you see?

26:20.456 --> 26:22.925
Jackie, what has
gotten into you?

26:23.659 --> 26:25.928
Luke, Grace is dead.

26:31.435 --> 26:33.602
Luke, wait!

26:33.636 --> 26:35.037
No one has to know.

26:47.350 --> 26:48.851
Hey, what happened.

26:49.585 --> 26:50.886
Where's the chick?

27:10.639 --> 27:13.576
Lucas, what are you doing
out here?

27:13.609 --> 27:15.978
I just, uh, needed
some fresh air.

27:16.612 --> 27:17.913
I'll see you inside, okay?

27:18.614 --> 27:20.916
Hey, I'm...
I'm really sorry, Luke.

27:20.950 --> 27:22.551
I hope you know
that I'm here for you.

27:24.153 --> 27:25.389
I do.

27:26.889 --> 27:27.923
Hey, Luke.

27:29.558 --> 27:31.428
It's okay to not be okay.

27:44.907 --> 27:46.242
I'm so sorry.

27:47.209 --> 27:48.544
I'm so sorry.

28:43.467 --> 28:45.801
What are you doing,
brother?

28:47.036 --> 28:48.671
Watching the game,
drinking a beer.

28:50.540 --> 28:52.608
Well, it looks like
you're wasting your life away.

28:52.641 --> 28:55.412
Yeah, well, looks can be
deceiving.

28:56.612 --> 28:58.448
You can't keep doing this
to yourself.

29:00.216 --> 29:02.051
And why is that, Chase?

29:02.084 --> 29:05.121
Because you're hurting
your family, your friends.

29:06.389 --> 29:07.591
This isn't you.

29:08.791 --> 29:09.825
People change.

29:10.993 --> 29:12.027
Not like this.

29:13.597 --> 29:15.599
Maybe exactly like this.

29:18.734 --> 29:23.473
Luke, when my wife left me,

29:23.507 --> 29:25.274
I felt like a penny
waiting for change.

29:26.476 --> 29:29.912
Your wife left you,
my wife died.

29:29.945 --> 29:32.348
I'm not saying
it's the exact same.

29:35.684 --> 29:37.319
All right...

29:38.821 --> 29:40.624
how did you get over your wife?

29:42.825 --> 29:43.859
I never did.

29:46.128 --> 29:47.631
She was my whole world.

29:48.964 --> 29:50.232
She took my dog.

29:52.268 --> 29:53.302
She took your dog?

29:53.335 --> 29:54.638
She took the damn dog.

29:59.775 --> 30:00.809
I miss that dog.

30:03.279 --> 30:05.214
Chase... and don't take
this the wrong way...

30:06.315 --> 30:09.752
I know you came over here
to make me feel better.

30:09.785 --> 30:11.754
I gotta be honest,
man, you suck at this.

30:11.787 --> 30:14.658
Aw, who am I kidding?

30:16.158 --> 30:18.794
Maybe I'm not the one
to help you through this.

30:18.827 --> 30:20.863
All I know is
the best way to get over someone

30:20.896 --> 30:23.199
is to get under someone else.

30:23.232 --> 30:24.867
Mason.

30:24.900 --> 30:26.702
What are you doing here?

30:26.735 --> 30:28.505
You guys surprised to see me?

30:28.538 --> 30:30.139
Well, yeah.

30:30.172 --> 30:32.975
I mean, you've been gone
for over a year,

30:33.008 --> 30:34.678
so I'd say so.

30:36.345 --> 30:37.780
When did you get back?

30:37.813 --> 30:39.416
Just now, came right here.

30:41.250 --> 30:44.688
That's great.
Um, what do you want, Mason?

30:44.720 --> 30:46.755
I'm here to help you
get your life back together.

30:47.323 --> 30:49.191
My life?

30:49.225 --> 30:52.529
Yeah, it's dead,
buried in the ground.

30:53.697 --> 30:55.130
No, that's your wife.

30:58.000 --> 30:59.034
Same difference.

31:01.737 --> 31:02.771
You know what?

31:04.840 --> 31:05.975
I'm gonna head outside
for a smoke.

31:07.577 --> 31:09.111
I'll give you boys
a minute to talk.

31:20.055 --> 31:22.925
What are you really
doing here, Mason?

31:22.958 --> 31:25.729
Lucas, I know
how much you love Grace.

31:25.761 --> 31:29.131
It's like one of those
Nicholas Sparks books.

31:30.132 --> 31:31.934
Nicholas Sparks?

31:31.967 --> 31:34.003
Yeah, like one
of those chick flicks.

31:34.036 --> 31:35.672
I know you loved her,
but she's gone.

31:37.273 --> 31:39.341
Tell me something
I don't know.

31:39.375 --> 31:40.410
You're not gone.

31:41.611 --> 31:43.779
You got plenty of life
left to live.

31:43.812 --> 31:47.082
I wake up every morning,
go to work, pay my bills.

31:47.983 --> 31:49.785
What else do I need to be doing?

31:51.086 --> 31:53.757
- You need to learn to live without Grace.
- Hmm.

31:57.560 --> 31:59.396
Ah! No, thanks.

31:59.429 --> 32:00.996
Everything's fine the way it is.

32:02.432 --> 32:03.466
This isn't you.

32:04.166 --> 32:06.235
This has never been you.

32:06.268 --> 32:08.471
You know, I'm getting
really sick and tired

32:08.505 --> 32:10.873
of people telling me
what isn't me.

32:10.906 --> 32:12.007
What is me, Mason?

32:13.309 --> 32:15.244
Is it the guy that goes
partying every night?

32:15.277 --> 32:17.480
How about the guy that goes out

32:17.514 --> 32:19.582
and gets laid by a different
chick every night of the week?

32:19.616 --> 32:21.718
You know what?
I'll spare you the suspense.

32:21.751 --> 32:24.721
That's not me anymore and it
hasn't been in a long time, so...

32:24.754 --> 32:28.257
I know that's not you,
not anymore.

32:28.290 --> 32:31.160
You're the guy who falls
in love with a great woman

32:31.193 --> 32:32.227
and gets married.

32:34.631 --> 32:37.933
Been there, done that,
didn't like how it ended.

32:37.966 --> 32:40.903
You're the guy who never gives
up, no matter how hard it gets.

32:40.936 --> 32:42.004
That's you, Lucas.

32:45.274 --> 32:47.209
Maybe this is me.

32:48.310 --> 32:50.012
You might want this to be you,

32:50.045 --> 32:52.114
but I'm not gonna
let that happen.

32:52.147 --> 32:54.116
Oh, you're not gonna
let that happen?

32:54.149 --> 32:57.319
Okay, so you're gonna just
swoop in and save the day?

32:57.353 --> 32:59.955
Yeah, maybe I will.

33:00.790 --> 33:03.025
And, uh, how are you
gonna do that?

33:06.563 --> 33:09.833
You got a date, Friday night.

33:11.967 --> 33:13.936
- Are you stupid?
- What?

33:13.969 --> 33:15.772
- I'm married!
- No, you're not.

33:15.805 --> 33:17.339
It's been a year.
It's time to move on.

33:19.007 --> 33:22.445
No! No, no, no, hell, no.
Mm-mm.

33:22.479 --> 33:25.080
Come on, man,
it's just one date.

33:26.348 --> 33:27.983
I'm not asking you to marry her.

33:28.016 --> 33:29.318
You need to get out
and test the waters.

33:29.351 --> 33:32.221
Dude, not happening.
Forget it.

33:32.254 --> 33:33.556
You need to do this.

33:36.925 --> 33:38.127
So, let me get this straight.

33:38.160 --> 33:40.195
You've been gone for a year.

33:40.229 --> 33:42.364
You just pop back in,
and all of a sudden

33:42.399 --> 33:43.867
you know what I need in my life?

33:46.703 --> 33:47.737
Let me ask you this.

33:48.937 --> 33:51.907
If Grace were here,
what would she want?

33:51.940 --> 33:54.477
Grace isn't here.

33:54.511 --> 33:55.545
Exactly.

35:21.664 --> 35:23.800
Obviously, you're gonna be
a little rusty tonight,

35:23.833 --> 35:26.469
so let's go over a few basics.

35:26.503 --> 35:28.438
Let's not.

35:28.471 --> 35:30.239
You know you can't bring up
Grace tonight, right?

35:31.508 --> 35:32.675
Can we not do this?

35:32.709 --> 35:34.444
I'm just saying,

35:34.477 --> 35:36.479
you haven't been on a date
in a long time.

35:37.514 --> 35:40.984
Don't worry,
I got it covered, hmm?

35:42.452 --> 35:44.387
I know I've been busting
your balls, but...

35:47.457 --> 35:48.525
I'm gonna be serious
for a minute.

35:50.960 --> 35:53.028
- Don't hurt yourself.
- Very funny.

35:55.965 --> 35:57.934
You remember when we
used to play video games?

35:59.134 --> 36:01.504
Do you mean when we were kids?

36:01.538 --> 36:03.006
Yeah, I guess.

36:03.038 --> 36:05.408
Good, so you remember me
beating you

36:05.441 --> 36:07.443
in <i>Street Fighter II</i>, right?

36:07.477 --> 36:09.012
- You didn't beat me.
- Yeah, I did.

36:09.044 --> 36:10.847
No, you didn't.

36:10.880 --> 36:12.782
The point is I used to beat you
all the time

36:12.815 --> 36:15.518
and you'd get all mad and cry,
and so we had to start over.

36:15.552 --> 36:17.020
I didn't cry.

36:17.052 --> 36:18.153
Then why did we call you
"cry-baby"?

36:18.186 --> 36:20.456
Because I liked that movie.

36:20.490 --> 36:23.893
Yeah,
keep telling yourself that.

36:24.861 --> 36:27.497
Okay, so this is
you being serious?

36:27.530 --> 36:30.533
Look, I know life
isn't a video game,

36:30.567 --> 36:32.702
but this is your chance
to hit the reset button.

36:33.870 --> 36:35.370
You make it sound so simple.

36:40.677 --> 36:41.711
Just one thing.

36:43.513 --> 36:44.547
What?

36:45.815 --> 36:47.282
You should probably
take off your wedding ring.

36:49.886 --> 36:53.255
Mason, I...

36:53.288 --> 36:54.323
I know. Believe me, I know.

36:56.025 --> 37:00.329
Just take it off for the date
and put it in your pocket.

37:00.362 --> 37:01.864
Put it on a necklace,
I really don't care.

37:01.898 --> 37:05.267
Just don't wear it
on your finger.

37:05.300 --> 37:07.570
I didn't even wanna
go on this date.

37:07.604 --> 37:09.539
You can put it back on the
minute the date's over, okay?

37:09.572 --> 37:10.607
Trust me on this one.

37:15.778 --> 37:19.616
Look, man, I... I get it, okay?

37:19.649 --> 37:23.686
And I know it's been
over a year, but...

37:28.057 --> 37:29.993
I'm not sure I'm ready for this.

37:31.561 --> 37:33.096
I guess we'll find out,
won't we?

37:41.904 --> 37:43.106
Lucas?

37:43.806 --> 37:44.841
Carla.

37:45.908 --> 37:46.943
That's me.

37:48.611 --> 37:49.779
It's nice to meet you.

37:49.812 --> 37:51.047
You as well.

37:55.183 --> 37:58.320
So, have you ever
been here before?

37:58.353 --> 38:01.958
Oh, no, but I've heard
really good things about it.

38:01.991 --> 38:05.128
Yeah, it kind of has
a cool vibe to it.

38:05.160 --> 38:06.896
Yeah, it does.

38:06.929 --> 38:07.964
Yes, it does.

38:15.672 --> 38:18.173
I don't care, I like the shrimp.

38:18.206 --> 38:22.177
You ordered last time.
It's my turn. I want the shrimp.

38:33.122 --> 38:34.991
I think you should get
whatever you want.

38:37.192 --> 38:38.226
Thank you.

38:41.130 --> 38:43.166
Hello, I'm Brian.
I'll be your server tonight.

38:43.198 --> 38:45.034
Can I get you two started
with something to drink?

38:45.068 --> 38:46.436
Oh, water is fine.

38:46.469 --> 38:47.503
Yes, it is.

38:50.473 --> 38:52.175
Water, yeah, that's, uh...
that's great.

38:54.209 --> 38:58.114
Are we ready to order
or do we need a few minutes?

38:58.147 --> 39:00.783
I don't care what he said,
I still want the shrimp.

39:07.523 --> 39:09.792
I think you should
get the shrimp.

39:09.826 --> 39:11.694
I'm sure it's great, right?

39:13.261 --> 39:16.132
Please, don't be rude.

39:17.567 --> 39:19.736
- I'm sorry?
- It's not polite.

39:21.104 --> 39:22.972
I'm gonna give you two
a few minutes.

39:23.005 --> 39:24.239
Yeah.

39:28.611 --> 39:30.213
Did I say something
to offend you?

39:32.081 --> 39:33.816
No, it's fine.

39:36.284 --> 39:38.521
Because I was just saying, like,

39:38.554 --> 39:41.424
you should just get
whatever you want.

39:41.457 --> 39:42.492
Thank you.

39:44.193 --> 39:46.729
I don't care what he said,
I still want the shrimp.

39:52.468 --> 39:53.569
You're kidding, right?

39:54.871 --> 39:57.006
Kidding you about what?

39:57.039 --> 39:59.108
This is a joke.

39:59.142 --> 40:01.343
Mason... Mason put you
up to this, didn't he?

40:01.376 --> 40:03.079
God. That Mason.

40:03.112 --> 40:04.614
Come out, Mason.

40:04.647 --> 40:07.517
Ha ha, really funny.
Joke's over.

40:07.550 --> 40:09.185
That's... This is good.
That's good.

40:10.119 --> 40:11.587
This isn't a joke.

40:17.059 --> 40:18.194
Oh...

40:20.630 --> 40:24.734
Sorry, I just assumed
this was a joke.

40:24.767 --> 40:28.538
I mean, one minute
you're talking to me,

40:28.571 --> 40:30.372
and then the next,
you're talking

40:30.406 --> 40:34.911
to what I can only assume
is an imaginary friend.

40:34.944 --> 40:38.948
I don't have
an imaginary friend.

40:38.981 --> 40:41.150
- Oh.
- Oh, my goodness.

40:41.184 --> 40:43.119
Yeah, I know. Rude much?

40:44.520 --> 40:45.555
Right there.

40:46.489 --> 40:48.090
What is your problem?

40:48.124 --> 40:51.394
Um, I'm not the one
with the problem.

40:51.427 --> 40:52.995
Really?

40:54.030 --> 40:57.500
'Cause you definitely seem
like you have a problem.

40:57.533 --> 41:00.136
Yeah, yeah, he definitely does.

41:01.537 --> 41:04.407
See, there! There it is again.

41:04.440 --> 41:06.008
Why are you being so mean?

41:06.042 --> 41:07.743
I'm not trying to be mean,

41:07.777 --> 41:10.680
but, I mean,
you're acting kind of crazy.

41:10.713 --> 41:15.685
Oh!

41:15.718 --> 41:21.991
Please, please, please,
don't call me crazy.

41:26.162 --> 41:28.598
What am I supposed
to call you when...

41:28.631 --> 41:31.968
You can call me by my name.
Mm-hmm.

41:32.001 --> 41:33.069
Okay.

41:34.670 --> 41:36.772
I'm sorry, I'm not
trying to be mean.

41:36.806 --> 41:39.976
It's just that, again,
one minute you're talking to me,

41:40.009 --> 41:43.446
and the next,
you're talking to whatever.

41:43.479 --> 41:45.715
I mean, it's a little crazy.

41:46.849 --> 41:50.353
I asked you not
to call me crazy!

41:52.488 --> 41:55.858
I hate when guys call me crazy!

41:59.262 --> 42:01.664
Carla, please relax.

42:01.697 --> 42:04.867
I may have gone too far.
I'm sorry.

42:06.035 --> 42:08.237
So... for... for what? What?

42:08.271 --> 42:10.006
Sorry for what?

42:10.039 --> 42:11.374
I know. I'm not crazy.

42:12.408 --> 42:14.410
I'm sorry if I offended you?

42:15.177 --> 42:16.979
Oh, offended me?

42:21.050 --> 42:25.254
You mean, for calling me crazy?

42:25.288 --> 42:28.824
Why would I be offended?
I mean, I'm not crazy.

42:28.858 --> 42:29.892
I'm not crazy.

42:31.694 --> 42:35.231
If I'm being honest,
you are acting a little crazy right now.

42:35.264 --> 42:39.235
Stop calling me crazy!

42:42.271 --> 42:43.306
I'm out.

42:46.642 --> 42:48.110
- You're leaving?
- Yup!

42:56.919 --> 43:00.690
Thanks for ruining our date.
You did ruin it.

43:00.723 --> 43:02.426
I didn't do anything.

43:04.627 --> 43:05.661
Whatever.

43:08.631 --> 43:10.466
Can I help you with anything?

43:10.499 --> 43:12.436
I'd like the shrimp.

43:16.672 --> 43:19.041
- Jeez.
- Oh, man.

43:20.676 --> 43:22.511
So, let me get this straight.

43:24.280 --> 43:26.549
You set Luke up with
someone who heard voices.

43:28.517 --> 43:30.454
Okay, I guess
it's time to come clean.

43:32.488 --> 43:35.925
Wait, are you serious?
You knew she heard voices?

43:35.958 --> 43:37.960
No, I didn't know
she heard voices.

43:37.994 --> 43:40.129
And I also didn't set you up
on the date.

43:40.162 --> 43:41.931
Wait, what?

43:41.964 --> 43:44.300
I did, and you're welcome, bro.

43:46.936 --> 43:48.904
- Are you kidding me?
- No.

43:48.938 --> 43:51.741
What? There's nothing
wrong with Carla.

43:51.774 --> 43:54.110
Yeah, she's a peach,

43:54.143 --> 43:57.179
you know, besides the fact
that she hears voices.

43:57.213 --> 44:01.117
Okay, I admit
she's a little crazy.

44:01.150 --> 44:02.685
A little crazy?

44:02.718 --> 44:04.687
Your boy set you up with someone

44:04.720 --> 44:06.922
who's two cans
short of a six-pack.

44:06.956 --> 44:09.525
- You just didn't give her a chance.
- Mm.

44:09.558 --> 44:10.760
Shut up, Terry.

44:12.795 --> 44:15.499
So, obviously, the date
didn't go as planned.

44:15.564 --> 44:18.100
I kind of expected it to be bad.

44:18.134 --> 44:20.903
Just not "she belongs
in a straitjacket" bad.

44:22.905 --> 44:24.040
Don't even worry about it.

44:25.674 --> 44:27.843
I already got you set up
on a second date.

44:27.877 --> 44:30.212
Yeah, there is no way
I'm going on another date

44:30.246 --> 44:31.680
with that woman.

44:31.714 --> 44:33.517
Not with her, someone else.

44:35.419 --> 44:37.387
I didn't even wanna
go on the first date.

44:37.421 --> 44:39.622
What would make you think
I'd want to go on another one?

44:39.655 --> 44:40.689
But your last date went so well.

44:42.191 --> 44:45.661
- Yeah, no more dates.
- Yeah, you are.

44:45.694 --> 44:47.630
Trust me, you'll like this one.

44:47.663 --> 44:50.132
Yeah, you'll like her...
till she starts talking to herself.

44:50.166 --> 44:53.669
Okay, forget about crazy Carla.

44:53.702 --> 44:56.406
This is a good girl.
You'll really like her.

44:56.440 --> 44:59.443
Nice, sweet, good-looking girl.
Trust me.

45:02.379 --> 45:04.213
Did you have a hand
in setting this one up too?

45:04.246 --> 45:07.417
Oh, my God, there is
nothing wrong with Carla.

45:07.451 --> 45:09.251
Your loss man.
I'm gonna call her.

45:12.456 --> 45:15.224
You know, I'm not one
to agree with Mason...

45:16.892 --> 45:18.861
but what have you got
to lose, brother?

45:18.894 --> 45:20.029
My sanity.

45:20.062 --> 45:23.165
So, it's settled.

45:23.199 --> 45:24.300
One more date.

45:26.570 --> 45:28.938
I'm gonna regret this, aren't I?

45:28.971 --> 45:30.906
Probably.

45:30.940 --> 45:32.775
Are you talking
to me now?

45:32.808 --> 45:34.743
Can you please be quiet?

45:34.777 --> 45:38.180
No, not you, you.
The other you!

45:39.483 --> 45:40.517
What?

45:42.618 --> 45:43.686
Match made in heaven.

46:02.271 --> 46:04.407
- Caroline.
- Hi.

46:04.441 --> 46:06.675
- Hi, I'm Lucas.
- Hi.

46:12.314 --> 46:14.216
Thank you again for meeting me
in the afternoon.

46:15.951 --> 46:18.287
I'm sure it's probably earlier
than you were expecting.

46:18.320 --> 46:20.055
Oh, no, it's fine.

46:20.089 --> 46:21.857
Daytime, nighttime,
I'm good with either.

46:23.359 --> 46:24.461
I'm glad to hear that.

46:25.928 --> 46:26.962
If I'm being honest,

46:28.130 --> 46:31.468
meeting in the daytime
works out better for me.

46:31.501 --> 46:34.437
I'm not much of a night owl.

46:34.471 --> 46:35.905
Early bird, huh?

46:35.938 --> 46:37.840
Good afternoon. I'm Liz.

46:37.873 --> 46:39.409
What can I get you guys
to drink?

46:39.442 --> 46:41.444
Oh, I'll have the sweet tea
if you have it.

46:41.478 --> 46:43.112
We sure do.

46:43.145 --> 46:44.914
- And for you?
- Water's fine, thank you.

46:44.947 --> 46:46.483
Great. Be right back.

46:49.985 --> 46:51.987
Do you mind if I ask you
a personal question?

46:54.123 --> 46:56.660
It's a little early
for personal questions, no?

46:58.395 --> 47:00.329
Oh, sorry.

47:02.031 --> 47:04.733
I'm messing with you.
Ask me anything you'd like.

47:07.169 --> 47:11.106
Okay, um, so, I guess
my question would be...

47:13.209 --> 47:15.945
do you accept Jesus Christ
as your Lord and savior?

47:17.012 --> 47:18.714
Oh. Um...

47:20.015 --> 47:22.385
Caroline,
that's a great question,

47:22.419 --> 47:26.690
but I'd prefer if we don't
discuss that right now.

47:28.190 --> 47:30.493
- Okay. Here you go.
- Thank you.

47:30.527 --> 47:31.894
All right,
are we ready to order?

47:31.927 --> 47:34.029
I'm sorry, not yet.

47:34.063 --> 47:35.699
Okay, I'll give you guys
a minute.

47:39.101 --> 47:40.704
So, you don't believe in God?

47:45.007 --> 47:48.811
I, um... I don't really know
how to answer that.

